Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Staufen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["South German: variant of   Stauffer  . Compare   Stoufer  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stoufer","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Staufer  ."]},{"name":"Stauffer","meanings":["South German:","occupational name for a maker or seller of beakers or mugs, from an agent derivative of Middle High German <i>stouf</i> ‘beaker, stoup’.","habitational name for someone from any of various minor places called with this word, for example Stauf, Staufen; the reference is to hills thought to resemble a beaker in shape. Compare   Stouffer  ."]}]},{"name":"Gottfried","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>god</i>, <i>got</i> ‘god’ + <i>frid</i> ‘peace’; borne by the 13th-century poet Gottfried von Strassburg."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ier","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and Norwegian vernacular form of   Peter ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peter","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Graf Gottfried Ier Von Staufen I was born in 1140, in Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Württemberg, Germany as the son of Count Adalbert VON STAUFEN and Spohnheum. He had at least 2 daughters with Marie de Boulogne. He died in 1177, in Germany, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1140–1177":"1140–1177","1141–1182":"1141–1182","1162–1252":"1162–1252","1164–1252":"1164–1252","1110–Male":"1110–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1177":"1177","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","Lower Saxony, Braunschweig, Niedersachsen, Germany":"Braunschweig, Niedersachsen, Saksamaa","Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Königreich Württemberg, Deutsches Reich":"Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Hohenstaufen Castle, Goeppingen, Germany":"Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1140–1177":"1140–1177","1141–1182":"1141–1182","1162–1252":"1162–1252","1164–1252":"1164–1252","1110–Male":"1110–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1177":"1177","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","Lower Saxony, Braunschweig, Niedersachsen, Germany":"Braunschweig, Niedersachsen, Saksa","Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Königreich Württemberg, Deutsches Reich":"Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Württemberg, Saksa","Hohenstaufen Castle, Goeppingen, Germany":"Hohenstaufen, Göppingen, Württemberg, Saksa","Germany":"Saksa"},"fr":{"1140–1177":"1140–1177","1141–1182":"1141–1182","1162–1252":"1162–1252","1164–1252":"1164–1252","1110–Male":"1110–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1177":"1177","1110":"1110","1164":"1164","1252":"1252","1141":"1141","1140":"1140","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","Lower Saxony, Braunsc